Barely 48-hours after his swearing in, Delta State Governor, Senator Arthur Okowa    has appointed Chiedu Ebbie, a former Commissioner for Education in the state as the secretary to the state government. Ebbie is from the same local government Area with the Delta State governor. Former Finance commissioner, David Edevbie, from Delta Central senatorial district was also appointed the Chief of Staff while Solomon Funkekeme was appointed Senior Political Adviser to the Governor. The trio are the first persons to be appointed into the new cabinet of the Governor, which commenced two days ago. Details later.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .